Sentencas: The mixed ionic and electronic conductors (MIEC) of La0.9Sr0.1Co0.8Ni0.2O3-delta (LSCN)-Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 (SDC) were investigated for potential application as a cathode material for solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) based on a SDC electrolyte.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of La0.9Sr0.1Co0.8Ni0.2O3-δ-Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 composite cathode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Electrochemical impedance spectroscopy (EIS) technique was performed over the temperature range of 600-850 degrees C to determine the cathode polarization resistance, which is represented by area specific resistance (ASR).
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of La0.9Sr0.1Co0.8Ni0.2O3-δ-Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 composite cathode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: This study systematically investigated the exchange current densities (i(o)) for oxygen reduction reaction (ORR), determined from the EIS data and high-field cyclic voltammetry.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of La0.9Sr0.1Co0.8Ni0.2O3-δ-Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 composite cathode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The 7OLSCN-30SDC composite cathode revealed a high exchange current density (i(0)) value of 297.6 mA/cm(2) at 800 degrees C determined by high-field technique.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of La0.9Sr0.1Co0.8Ni0.2O3-δ-Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 composite cathode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: This suggested that the triple phase boundary (TPB) may spread over more surface of this composite cathode and revealing a high catalytically active surface area.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of La0.9Sr0.1Co0.8Ni0.2O3-δ-Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 composite cathode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The activation energies (E-a) of ORR determined from the slope of Arrhenius plots for EIS and high-field techniques are 96.9 kJ mol(-1) and 90.4 kJ mol(-1), respectively.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of La0.9Sr0.1Co0.8Ni0.2O3-δ-Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 composite cathode for solid oxide fuel cells
